        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <ul id="privacy">
            <p>At Exscimula, we respect your privacy. This policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your
                personal information when you use our services.</p><br>

            <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Personal Data:</strong> Includes name, email, and other contact info when you register or
                    use certain features.</li>
                <li><strong>Non-personal Data:</strong> Includes browser info, IP address, and usage data for analytics.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> We use cookies to improve your experience on our site.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>To provide and improve our services.</li>
                <li>To send updates or promotional materials.</li>
                <li>For site analytics to enhance your experience.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>3. Sharing Your Information</h3>
            <li>We do not sell or rent your data. We may share data with trusted partners or if required by law.</li>
            <br>

            <h3>4. Data Security</h3>
            <li>We take steps to protect your data but cannot guarantee complete security of information transmitted
                online.</li><br>

            <h3>5. Your Choices</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Access and update your data anytime through your account.</li>
                <li>Opt-out of promotional emails by unsubscribing.</li>
                <li>Manage cookies through your browser settings.</li>
            </ul>
        </ul><br>

        <h1>Contribution Policy</h1>
        <ul id="contribution">
            <h3>1. Content Relevance</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Only upload simulations related to natural science experiments.</li>
                <li>Ensure that your content is educational, informative, and aligned with the educational goals of
                    Exscimula.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2. Accuracy and Integrity</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Simulations should be accurate and scientifically sound.</li>
                <li>Ensure all variables, procedures, and results are well-documented and reflect established scientific
                    knowledge.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>3. Intellectual Property</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Only upload content that you have created or have the necessary rights to share.</li>
                <li>Provide proper attribution for any third-party resources used (e.g., images, data sets, or
                    software).</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4. Quality of Content</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Ensure that your simulation runs smoothly without errors. If the simulation involves code, it should
                    be free from bugs and should work across multiple platforms.</li>
                <li>Provide clear instructions for users to understand how to interact with the simulation.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>5. Appropriate Behavior</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Contributions must adhere to respectful and professional conduct. No inappropriate, offensive, or
                    harmful content will be tolerated.</li>
                <li>Users must refrain from uploading any content that may disrupt or harm the integrity of the platform
                    or other users.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>6. User Interaction</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Encourage a collaborative and supportive community. Provide feedback when requested and participate
                    in discussions in a constructive manner.</li>
                <li>Do not upload content that forces users to interact in a way that is not voluntary.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>7. Data Privacy and Security</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Ensure that no personal data or private information is included in the simulations or shared during
                    the interaction with them.</li>
                <li>Follow all applicable privacy laws regarding data collection and sharing.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>8. Review and Approval</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>All simulations will be reviewed by the Exscimula team before being published on the site.</li>
                <li>Simulations that do not meet these guidelines may be rejected or removed after publication.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>9. Modifications and Updates</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>The Exscimula team reserves the right to modify the contribution policy as needed.</li>
                <li>Contributors will be notified of major updates to this policy.</li>
            </ul><br><br>

            <p>By uploading content to Exscimula, you agree to follow these guidelines and help us maintain a
                high-quality, reliable, and engaging platform for learning and discovery.</p><br>

            <p>Thank you for contributing to Exscimula!</p><br>
        </ul>
